article_title: 237 years later, George Washington is still crossing the Delaware River – The Denver Post
article_text: Swarms of insects breeding in a polluted river near the Taj Mahal are threatening the intricate marble inlay work at the 17th century monument to love by leaving green and black patches of waste on its walls, archaeological experts said Monday.
